content:
Despicable Me (2010) was the first Illumination Entertainment Movie that I've seen and it's the first one that I saw in the theater. Since then, this movie has turned into one of the most successful and insane movie franchise in Hollywood. Despite its numerous issues, I still love this movie for all of its flaws 14 years later.Positives for Despicable Me (2010):
This movie knows how to have fun with its premise to the point where it has become one of the most endlessly rewatchable movies of all time. I also really enjoy a lot of the characters in the movie. Steve Carrell is awesome as Gru where even though this guy is a villain you just can't help yourself but love him for all his villainy and asides from Over the Hedge (2006), this was the movie that introduced me to Steve Carrell and what he can bring as a main character which a lot of other people already knew during his time in The Office (2005-2013). I will say this it's odd to see and hear Michael Scott talk about evil plans after binge watching The Office for the first time over a month ago. I also liked Margo, Edith and Agnes in this movie as they are basically helping Gru change his ways by the end of the movie. It is also worth noting that I watched this movie in the theater because Margo was voiced by Miranda Cosgrove, who I only knew as Carly Shay from iCarly (2007-2012). Also, it is very interesting to see and hear both Michael Scott and Carly Shay butting heads with each other. Jason Segel as Vector was a great villain as he was both very calculating and funny. I also really enjoyed Russell Brand as Dr. Nefario. And of course, we can't talk about this movie without talking about the Minions themselves as they are the reason why so many people are obsessed with these movies. The Minions are those characters who add that extra level of fun that this movie needs and also their scenes are very funny.Negatives for Despicable Me (2010);
Now these negatives don't bother me with this first movie, but they are definitely worth pointing out. First of all, this movie marks the beginning of what people like to called the Illuminationisms that present in all of the movies made by Illumination Entertainment. First of all, you have characters using some of the most ludicrous stuff that you'll ever see in any movie. You also have the movie soundtrack containing radio hit songs that a lot of people, specifically the adults, get annoying and tired of constantly hearing. And finally, Gru's arc in this movie is very predictable cause from the moment when he adopts Margo, Edith and Agnes, it is made so obvious how the movie is going to play out throughtout the rest of the runtime.Overall, Despicable Me (2010) is a phenomenal movie that I continue to love ever since I saw it over 14 years ago and while there are elements that definitely will bother some people, it's still a movie where the whole family can have fun watching.
